\begin_layout Standard
The study of our genes, and the molecular biology therein, has uncovered
 a complex world of DNA and proteins that interact to control gene expression.
 Gene expression involves a variety of proteins to work together to initiate
 transcription.
 An important type of protein are transcription factorswhich bind to short
 sequences of the DNA and thereby regulate the nearby genes.
 Identifying the transcription factor binding sites has become an important
 problem for understanding gene regulation.
 Gene regulation studies have benefitted massively from new high throughput
 technology, including microarray and next-generation sequencing.
 These technologies are able to provide a whole- genome persepctive on gene
 regulation.
 These new platforms have given us a huge amount of data that provides a
 whole-genome perspective of this process.
 
